      "id": "PopularPost190511",
      "post_content": "@A3Kitsune: I beg to differ. In those days, you would have needed [Sleight of Mind](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sleight of Mind) (a blue card) to make this playable (side-board not withstanding). Deathgrip is black because of the pure evilness of it once you've sleighted it to your opponent's color. If you're actually playing against a green deck, then death counters life. Makes sense to me at least.\n  \n   \nHere's a recipe for a fun, casual deck I built that utilizes Deathgrip:\n  \n   \nGloom-grip Lockdown:\n  \n   \nLand (23):\n  \n1x [Plains](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Plains)   \n6x [Island](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Island)   \n6x [Swamp](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Swamp)   \n1x [Seachrome Coast](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Seachrome Coast)   \n1x [Sejiri Refuge](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sejiri Refuge)   \n3x [Jwar Isle Refuge](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Jwar Isle Refuge)   \n1x [Underground River](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Underground River)   \n1x [Roo\\*\\*\\*er Depths](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Roo***er Depths)   \n1x [Orzhov Basilica](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Orzhov Basilica)   \n1x [Caves of Koilos](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Caves of Koilos)   \n1x [Terramorphic Expanse](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Terramorphic Expanse)   \n   \nWhite (1):\n  \n1x [Enlightened Tutor](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Enlightened Tutor)   \n   \nBlue (20):\n  \n4x ... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "Opeth2010",
